node.text:
Myself, @eglpuds along with Former Mayor Kasim Reed are joining forces to help with school supplies. I can not be in this community and not serve the community. I was able to connect with @kasimreed yesterday and  ask a lot of questions. We spoke at about POLICE BRUTALITY and his plan for the future, We spoke about GENTRIFICATION and the displacement of small black businesses, we spoke at length about Homelessness and the WEALTH EQUALITY GAP, AFFORDABLE HOUSING AND YOUTH EMPLOYMENT.  ALL of my concerns were his concerns and he actually had plans of action that would truly change what the ATLANTA community looks like. I don’t blindly support anyone so it was important for me to hear his point of view and plans. There is a link in my bio to help get him elected. Please click and support his campaign. 
.
@yelleskincare Store Give Away
55 Upper Alabama
Atlanta, GA 303030
1pm- Until supplies are gone.

node.text:
Myself along with @eglpuds and @kasimreed will be giving out @blendeddesigns back packs this Saturday starting at 1 until supplies run out. 

If you’re not in Atlanta please support this small, black owned, woman owned business. She almost lost her business due to covid and schools being shut down. They’re trying their best to hold on but it will all depend on how well they do during this back to school season. 

Every year the owner @iamcaseyrkelley donates thousands of back packs to my non profit @eglpuds. This year Instead of her donating, I purchased them because she needs the support. 

So y’all be sure that we spend all that back to school money in the right place and help @blendeddesigns stay  afloat. 

And if you are in A-town come see me this Saturday at the Yelle store. I’ll be giving out back packs to adults with children, while supplies last.

node.title: Back to School Give Away X @yelleskincare Store

node.text:
Myself, @eglpuds along with Former Mayor Kasim Reed are joining forces to help with school supplies. I can not be in this community and not serve the community. I was able to connect with @kasimreed yesterday and  ask a lot of questions. We spoke at about POLICE BRUTALITY and his plan for the future, We spoke about GENTRIFICATION and the displacement of small black businesses, we spoke at length about Homelessness and the WEALTH EQUALITY GAP, AFFORDABLE HOUSING AND YOUTH EMPLOYMENT.  ALL of my concerns were his concerns and he actually had plans of action that would truly change what the ATLANTA community looks like. I don’t blindly support anyone so it was important for me to hear his point of view and plans. There is a link in my bio to help get him elected. Please click and support his campaign. 
.
@yelleskincare Store Give Away
55 Upper Alabama
Atlanta, GA 303030
1pm- Until supplies are gone.

node.text:
Myself along with @eglpuds and @kasimreed will be giving out @blendeddesigns back packs this Saturday starting at 1 until supplies run out. 

If you’re not in Atlanta please support this small, black owned, woman owned business. She almost lost her business due to covid and schools being shut down. They’re trying their best to hold on but it will all depend on how well they do during this back to school season. 

Every year the owner @iamcaseyrkelley donates thousands of back packs to my non profit @eglpuds. This year Instead of her donating, I purchased them because she needs the support. 

So y’all be sure that we spend all that back to school money in the right place and help @blendeddesigns stay  afloat. 

And if you are in A-town come see me this Saturday at the Yelle store. I’ll be giving out back packs to adults with children, while supplies last.
